ce:section.ce:para:
In these equations, Ka is similar to the associative binding constant at the relating temperature T, and R is the gas constant, separately. A decent straight relationship ln Ka versus 1/T was existed. Thus, the values of ΔH, ∆S, and ∆G were calculated according to the linear regression equation inserted in Fig. 4a, b and c. The calculated values ∆H, ∆S and ∆G were all shown Table 3
                           . The negative value of ∆G demonstrates the binding procedure of CDs and serum albumins were spontaneous, and negative value of ∆H showed that the binding process of CDs and serum albumins was energy-releasing in nature, which recommend that higher the temperature, the weaker the interaction among CDs and serum albumins (Fig. 5
                           ).
